nVentory - Ruby on Rails Datacenter Inventory Manager - http://nventory.sourceforge.net

** This is still Alpha quality code and under heavy development **
We use it, we modify it a lot, and we understand how it works.
Your mileage may vary. 
But it's pretty cool so far and getting cooler.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You need to have a fully working Ruby on Rails setup first, obviously.

I like this guide: http://blog.codahale.com/2006/06/19/time-for-a-grown-up-server-rails-mongrel-apache-capistrano-and-you/

You will need the RedCloth gem

You should use Capistrano or some other method of deploying this application
(You could also try: rake db:migrate RAILS_ENV="production" )

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
** First LOGIN **
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Once installed, you can login with username/password of admin/admin

If you get to the dashboard, you have a working nVentory system.

You can click "Setup Sample Data" on the Dashboard if you want to populate your database with some demo data, node types, racks, IPs, etc etc, to take a look around the application.

